article.description: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 63, St. Francis, Pa. 56
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 63, St. Francis, Pa. 56
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 63, St. Francis, Pa. 56
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Lamar Trice scored 18 points and Danny Thompson added his first career double-double to lead Mount St. Mary's to a 63-56 win over Saint Francis (Pa.) on Thursday night. In a game of dueling losing streaks, Mount St. Mary's ended its eight-game skid while extending Saint Francis' to 10. Mount St. Mary's (4-12, 2-1 Northeast Conference) raced to a 19-point, first-half lead. Julian Norfleet's free throw with 2:22 left in the half gave the Mountaineers their biggest advantage, 36-17, before the Red Flash (2-12, 0-3) rallied. Down 37-22 at the half, the Red Flash cut the deficit to 53-50 on an Anthony Ervin jumper with 50 seconds left. Thompson, who had 10 points and 12 rebounds, answered with a dunk with 35 seconds left. Josh Castellanos also had 10 points for the Mountaineers. Mislav Jukic paced Saint Francis with 19 points and Umar Shannon added 16.
